docs.lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY, Nov. 20 -- While the press today celebrated yesterday's agreements with the United States, observers here studied their economic and political implications. Their consensus was that the agreements revealed Mexico's complete economic dependence upon the United States, which Mexico had turned to diplomatic advantage.

headline.main: MEXICO HEARTENED BY ACCORD WITH US; Closer Economic and Military Ties Are Expected to Result From the Agreement

docs.lead_paragraph: THE Brooklyn Symphony Orchestra, which made its bow ten days ago, is being sponsored by the Brooklyn Institute of Arts and Sciences in the hope that it will become a permanent institution, for the borough has not had a regular symphony orchestra since Theodore Thomas dealt the old Brooklyn Philharmonic a death blow by leaving it to organize the Chicago Symphony Orchestra in 1891.
